hivis.data

Interface DataTable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataSet
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TableView
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataTable, AbstractTableView, DataTableDefault, TableViewAppend, TableViewFilterRows, TableViewFunction, TableViewSeries, TableViewSeriesBase, TableViewTranspose

    public interface DataTable
extends DataSet
    Represents a table of data in which the columns are represented as DataSeries.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

      • selectSeriesRE

        TableView selectSeriesRE(Pattern pattern,
                         String renamePattern)
        Get a view of this table containing the series whose labels match the given regular expression, renaming the series with the given rename pattern.
        Parameters:
        pattern - The regular expression pattern to use to match series labels.
        renamePattern - The replacement pattern (with $N referring to capture groups in 'pattern'). If renamePattern contains '\\oi' or '\\ni' it will be replaced by the original or new index of the series respectively. An '\\oi' or '\\ni' may be followed by numerals to indicate an offset, for example "my\\ni5pf" will give strings "my5pf", my6pf", "my7pf" and so on.
        Returns:
        a view of this table containing the specified series in the order they appear in this table, renamed according the renamePattern.

      • relabelSeries

        TableView relabelSeries(String... labels)
        Get a view of this table containing the series in this table renamed with the specified labels. The number of labels given must match the numbers of series in the table.
        Parameters:
        labels - The new labels.

      • relabelSeriesPP

        TableView relabelSeriesPP(String prefix,
                          String postfix)
        Get a view of this table containing the series in this table renamed by prepending and appending the specified prefix and postfix to the labels. If the prefix or postfix contain '\\oi' this will be replaced by the (original) index of the series. An '\\oi' may be followed by numerals to indicate an offset, for example "my\\oi5pf" will give strings "my5pf", my6pf", "my7pf" and so on.
        Parameters:
        prefix - The string to prepend to each label. May be null or an empty string.
        postfix - The string to append to each label. May be null or an empty string.

      • apply

        TableView apply(TableFunction function,
                boolean includeOriginalSeries)
        Get a table containing series generated by applying the given function to this table.
        Parameters:
        function - The function to generate the series for the new table.
        includeOriginalSeries - Whether to include the DataSeries from this DataTable in the new table.
        Returns:
        a table containing series generated by applying the given function to this table, optionally including the series from this table.

      • transpose

        TableView transpose()
        Get a transposed view of this table. If a row key series is set in this table and it contains no duplicate values it will be used for the series labels in the transposed table, otherwise the row index will be used for the series label in the transposed table (see setRowKey(int)). The series labels for this table will become the row key in the transposed table.

      • append

        TableView append(DataTable table)
        Get a table view comprising the series in the given table appended to the series in this table. If the series labels (both presence and order) or types do not match then an error will occur.
